{{Orphan|date=December 2010}}

'''Futi''' is the first Portuguese [[electric vehicle]] made by [[António Febra]]'s company FUTI.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ecobelo.com/en_default.asp |title='FUTI - Carros Eléctricos |accessdate=2009-06-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100828064209/http://ecobelo.com/en_default.asp |archivedate=2010-08-28 |df= }}</ref> It runs exclusively on electric power and can be charged at home.

According to António Febra himself in an interview for [[Televisão Independente|TVI]] television channel, it was scheduled to be commercialized by June 2009. It was to cost between 13000 and 16000 Euros depending on battery option. [[Sociedade Independente de Comunicação|SIC]] also covered this story. Both channels featured footage of António Febra driving Futi on public roads.

Futi is also fully recyclable.

==Specifications==

* Electric Motor: 15 KW nominal.
* Dimensions: 2,684 long by 1,400 meters wide by 1,600 height
* Weight: about {{convert|400|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}
* Maximum speed: 1st version {{convert|48|km/h|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}, 2nd version {{convert|80|km/h|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}
* Autonomy: 80&nbsp;km, 120&nbsp;km, 150&nbsp;km or 200&nbsp;km

