The '''Johannesburg Renewable Energy Coalition''', also known as '''JREC''', is the group of countries supporting the Declaration on The Way Forward on Renewable Energy<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ec.europa.eu/environment/jrec/pdf/jrec_declaration.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-01-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080720104043/http://ec.europa.eu/environment/jrec/pdf/jrec_declaration.pdf |archivedate=2008-07-20 |df= }}</ref> (also known as the JREC Declaration), made at the [[Earth Summit 2002|World Summit on Sustainable Development]] in [[Johannesburg]], [[South Africa]], in September 2002. The JREC is co-chaired by the [[European Commission]] and the Government of [[Morocco]].

