{{Use Australian English|date=October 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Infobox Australian place | type = protected | name = Leven Beach Conservation Park | state = sa | iucn_category = iii | image = | caption = | image_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|34|54|25|S|137|11|59|E|display=inline,title}} | force_national_map = | relief = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_label_position = | map_alt = | nearest_town_or_city = [[Point Turton, South Australia|Point Turton]] | area = {{convert| 470|ha|acres|abbr=on}} | area_footnotes = <ref name=ReserveList>{{cite web|title=Protected Areas Information System - reserve list (as of 17 Feb 2014)|url=http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/files/b88e6e26-4bd9-4c68-8fff-9e800114eb69/park-management-protected-areas-gen.pdf|publisher=Department of Environment Water and Natural Resources|accessdate=26 March 2014|pages=}}</ref><!-- If the area is greater than 100ha (1km2) a conversion template is not required. --> | established = 23 June 1988 | established_footnotes = <ref name=ReserveList/> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_footnotes = | managing_authorities = [[Department of Environment, Water and Natural Resources (South Australia)|Department of Environment, Water and Natural Resources]] | url = }} '''Leven Beach Conservation Park''' is a [[protected area]] in the Australian state of [[South Australia]] located on the north coast of the lower part of [[Yorke Peninsula]] within the boundaries of the gazetted localities of [[Point Souttar, South Australia|Point Souttar]] and [[The Pines, South Australia|The Pines]] about {{convert|10|km|abbr=off}} west north-west of [[Point Turton, South Australia|Point Turton]].<ref name=PLB>{{cite web|title=Search result for "Leven Beach Conservation Park" (Record no SA0039233) with the following layers being selected - "Suburbs and Localities" and "Place names (gazetteer)" |url=http://maps.sa.gov.au/plb/# |publisher=Government of South Australia |date= |accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>
The conservation park was proclaimed in 1988 for the purpose of conserving ‘sheoak woodland and potentially provides habitat for a nationally endangered species of butterfly, the [[Hesperilla flavescens|Yellowish Sedge-skipper Butterfly]]’.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mainland Conservation Parks of Yorke Peninsula Management Plan 2009|url=http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/files/40ccb65e-c97a-4f04-af74-9e4f00b16e48/mainland-cps-of-yp-mp.pdf|publisher=Department for Environment and Heritage|accessdate=15 July 2014|page=2}}</ref>
The conservation park is classified as an [[International Union for Conservation of Nature|IUCN]] [[IUCN protected area categories#Category III — Natural Monument or Feature|Category III protected area]].<ref name=CAPAD2012SASum>{{cite web|title=CAPAD 2012 South Australia Summary (see 'DETAIL' tab)|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/system/files/pages/0f927a4e-336a-490c-a896-ec37874a5c73/files/capad2012sa.xlsx|work=CAPAD 2012|publisher=Australian Government - Department of the Environment|accessdate=6 February 2014|date=6 February 2014}}</ref>
