{{Infobox mountain | name = Mount Livadiyskaya | photo = Pidan.jpg | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 1332 | prominence = | listing = | location = [[Primorsky Krai]], [[Russia]] | range = [[Livadiysky Range]] | coordinates = | topo = | type = | age = | last_eruption = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Mount Livadiyskaya''' ({{lang-ru|гора́ Ливади́йская}} or {{lang|ru|со́пка Ливади́йская}}), unofficially known as '''Mount Pedan''' ({{lang|ru|Педа́н}}) or '''Mount Pidan''' ({{lang|ru|Пида́н}}) is one of the highest peaks in [[Shkotovsky District]] of [[Primorsky Krai]], [[Russia]].
Livadiyskaya is a part of the [[Livadiysky Range]] of the [[Sikhote-Alin]].
The history of the mountain is often mystified, due to the presence of [[megalith]]s. These attract adepts of different [[neopagan]] and other faiths.
The mountain is a popular hiking spot, which has seen a surge in the number of ascensions in recent years. This has resulted in worsening contamination.
